Floki Flamehair.wav.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Beneath the pine and iron sky,
where ravens stitch the morning,
I watched the ember in your hair
outshine the frost of warning.
They called you Floki Flame-hair,
wild fire in the snow—
but every blaze must bow at last
to quieter winds that blow.

[Chorus]
Oh Floki Flamehair, do you hear me?
Over sea-foam, over stone?
I sing your name into the long dark,
so you will not walk alone.
If the world is wide and merciless,
let this small song be kind—
a thread of gold, a sailor’s prayer,
a light you leave behind.

[Verse 2]
You walked the wolf-road, south and west,
with salt upon your collar,
a wanderer with weathered hands
and vows you would not hollow.
The mead-halls warmed behind your back,
yet still you chose the night,
as if the stars were sweeter bread
than any hearth could bite.

[Chorus]
Oh Floki Flamehair, do you hear me?
Over sea-foam, over stone?
I sing your name into the long dark,
so you will not walk alone.
If the world is wide and merciless,
let this small song be kind—
a thread of gold, a sailor’s prayer,
a light you leave behind.

[Verse 3]
Your blade was bright as winter sun
on shields along the river,
but softer was the way you held
a child’s fear from a shiver.
You never feared the bleeding edge,
nor storm’s unbraided roar—
yet I saw sorrow in your eyes
when gulls turned back to shore.

[Chorus]
Oh Floki Flamehair, do you hear me?
Over sea-foam, over stone?
I sing your name into the long dark,
so you will not walk alone.
If the world is wide and merciless,
let this small song be kind—
a thread of gold, a sailor’s prayer,
a light you leave behind.

[Bridge]
Lantern of ember,
anchor of ash,
heart made of tinder
under a sash.
You chase the horizon
with nothing to claim,
but every road remembers
the footsteps of flame.

[Chorus – Reprise]
Oh Floki Flamehair, come back to morning,
or rest where quiet waters run.
If you cannot return in body,
return as song, return as sun.
And when my hands grow old and empty,
when my voice is thin as wind,
I’ll still send your name through snowfall—
Floki… my silver, my kin.

[Outro]
Across the fjord, the fire dies low,
but in the dark it glows.
Floki Flamehair…
Floki Flamehair…
walk gently where the north wind goes.
